sec.p:
The transition from one state to another is a normal process due to learning (with the consequent development of brain areas), feeling emotions, or ageing. A normal time evolution is described with paths within the “healthy states” subspace, see the bottom right side of Fig. 2, where the “healthy evolution” brings a brain of a person generically indicated as A, in a healthy state \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
